<br>
1) No buffs. Hard to OE the bow, hard to even equip some very high level bows at all.<br>
<br>
2) Bow availability. If you REALLY want to do this, you almost have to have an existing cache of bows. One reason my bow MA got deleted was lack of bows. I've since rectified that situation for my bow MP and now have quite a store of Schuylers, sapphistics, limb bows (gah), and even a few pow and tube bows. Reets are available from stores and probably best bet for starting out. <br>
<br>
It's an interesting class variant, but develops VERY differently from a garden variety MA. Worth doing, if you like the challenge and just being a bit out of the ordinary. I suspect, however, it works better at low levels than at high level.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kung Fu MASTAH</span><br>  Posts: 650<br> <font color=#660000>(10/12/02 10:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2138.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some questions on bows</span><hr size=1> Well, said, Alecto, and I completely agree.<br>
